Day 6: SQL – DML (INSERT / UPDATE / DELETE)

Topic:
SQL Data Manipulation Language (DML)

Learning Objectives:

Understand how to insert, update, and delete data in database tables
Learn the difference between single-row and multiple-row insertion
Practice updating records using conditions
Understand safe deletion practices to avoid accidental data loss

Activities / Deliverables:

Populate all 5 tables created in VolyoDB with sample data
Write and execute 10 DML statements
Practice INSERT for single and multiple records
Use UPDATE with WHERE conditions to modify specific records
Use DELETE queries safely on selected rows
Verify all changes using SELECT statements

Tools / Tech:

MySQL 8
MySQL Workbench

